_Pa’al_ Imperative for regular shorushim:
The [[{{_pa’al_ imperative}} form]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|            | *Masculine* | *Feminine* |
| *Singular* | כְּתֹב <br><br> _ksov!_ <br><br><br> [to a man] write! | כִּתְבִי <br><br> _kisvi!_ <br><br><br> [to a woman] write! |
| *Plural*   | כִּתְבוּ <br><br> _kisvu!_ <br><br><br> [to men] write! | כְּתֹבְנָה <br><br> _ksovnau!_ <br><br><br> [to women] write! |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ת, and ב above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
